Ask HN: Open-source front end-as-a-service tools that don't try to own auth?
text:
I've poured over the tools (open source or otherwise) for rapidly developing web apps

- Retool

- Appsmith

- Budibase

- Baserow

and many more. The problem is, in addition to building your frontends, they all try to control user authentication/authorization. I think it's because that's how they charge for the product, so they can charge based on seats.

I already have a backend that's exposing an API with auth. I'd like something that just helps me rapidly drag and drop out controls, forms, tables, etc to develop my small web app.

Does nothing exist like this?

Show HN: Deltx – AI-Powered CFO for SMEs
text:
Hey HN! We're excited to share our project, Deltx, a finance management solution for small and medium-sized businesses that adds no extra work for the company owner. Deltx aims to save money, simplify financial tracking, and provide data-driven insights using AI technology.

Key features:

Burn Rate Creep Control: Track and manage recurring bills and subscriptions to reduce unnecessary expenses.

Simplified Financial Monitoring: User-friendly interface on top of your accounting software for easy spending and revenue tracking.

AI-Powered Insights: Leverage GPT-3/4 to serve as a virtual CFO, answering financial questions instantly for better decision-making.

We built Deltx to address the challenges SMEs face when managing their finances, especially when dealing with complex accounting software and making data-driven decisions. With Deltx, businesses can focus on growth while ensuring their finances are under control.

We'd love to get feedback from the HN community and answer any questions you might have. If you're interested in trying Deltx, we invite you to sign up for a free trial on our website: https://www.deltx.io/

Looking forward to your thoughts and suggestions!
